1
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:09,400
In Bhagavad-gītā
He says, “Among the daityās”,

2
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:13,650
means ”the demons”,
”among the demons”.

3
00:00:13,650 --> 00:00:17,100
When [in] Kṛṣṇa’s ... 
[in the] vibhuti chapter:

4
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:20,230
the different ‘of these I am that’,
‘of these I am that’.

5
00:00:20,410 --> 00:00:24,600
 
[Among the Demons]

6
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:27,950
It says, “Of the daityās, 
the demons,

7
00:00:27,950 --> 00:00:31,190
I am the devoted Prahlāda.”

8
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:37,300
So, we hear at one point that

9
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:44,190
Hiraṇyakaśipu’s wife
Kayādhu is pregnant with Prahlāda,

10
00:00:44,330 --> 00:00:50,380
but it’s unknown to the gods
that it’s Prahlāda Mahārāj.

11
00:00:50,380 --> 00:00:58,490
They kidnap her and want 
to engage in infanticide.

12
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,600
Have the baby born
and then kill

13
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,800
thinking he’ll be a great demon,
the son of Hiraṇyakaśipu.

14
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:08,300
Nārada Muni comes and says,
“No, actually this is a great devotee.”

15
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:12,800
How great? We also hear
in the Bhāgavatam:

16
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:17,900
svayambhūr nāradaḥ śambhuḥ
kumāraḥ kapilo manuḥ

17
00:01:17,900 --> 00:01:23,100
prahlādo janako bhīṣmo
balir vaiyāsakir vayam
[SB: 6.3.20]

18
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:27,400
He is listed as one 
of the 12 mahājanas.

19
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:29,700
The great,

20
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:34,700
dharmasya tattvaṁ nihitaṁ guhāyām
mahājano yena gataḥ sa panthāḥ
[Cc: 2.17.186]
 

21
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:39,700
The great devotees who are
 

22
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:45,000
delivering real, 
substantial religion.

23
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:50,340
So, Prahlāda is born
and parallel to that Śiśupāla,

24
00:01:50,340 --> 00:01:54,990
who, when he is a toddler,
he’s blaspheming Kṛṣṇa.

25
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:59,100
We’re told, when Prahlāda 
went to school,

26
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:02,500
you know, 
the Sanskrit alphabet

27
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:06,900
begins with ‘ka’, 
that’s the first letter.

28
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:11,100
‘ka’, ‘kha’ … ‘ja’, ‘jha’, ‘ña’ …
‘pa’, ‘pha’, ‘ba’, ‘bha’, ‘ma’, etc.

29
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:13,300
Like, we have ABC’s,

30
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,400
I don’t know what
they have in Russian,

31
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:18,060
but in English 
they have ABC’s.

32
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:21,200
Here ‘ka’, 
when he’d say ‘ka’,

33
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:24,000
his body would start
trembling, he’d be: ‘k- … k- …’

34
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,200
because it made
him think of Kṛṣṇa.

35
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,700
Even hearing the alphabet,

36
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:34,390
Prahlāda Mahārāj 
is so exalted in consciousness,

37
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:37,180
that he thought of Kṛṣṇa,
and he would go into

38
00:02:37,180 --> 00:02:43,720
an ecstatic swoon 
in front of his classmates,

39
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:47,400
whom he told, when 
he would preach to them,

40
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:52,600
kaumāra ācaret prājño
dharmān bhāgavatān iha
[SB: 7.6.1]

41
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,600
When should you take up
Kṛṣṇa consciousness?

42
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:58,400
Sometimes in India they say,
“Dharma, artha, kāma, mokṣa”.

43
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:01,200
First you do dharma
up to the age of 25,

44
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:05,200
then artha, 25,
and kāma up to 50,

45
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:08,900
then retire and then 
maybe,

46
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:16,090
when you are in your 
mid 50s, late 60s—mokṣa.

47
00:03:16,090 --> 00:03:18,600
Somehow that part
never happens.

48
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:21,600
50s, 60s, 70s …

49
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:24,800
it’s going far
and far, recedes...

50
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,680
That’s not what 
Prahlāda Mahārāj says.

51
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,300
Prahlāda Mahārāj says,

52
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:33,260
kaumāra ācaret prājño
dharmān bhāgavatān iha
[SB: 7.6.1]

53
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:36,800
You should take up Kṛṣṇa consciousness 
as soon as possible—

54
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,900
preferably in childhood,

55
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:42,300
when you are a child.

56
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:48,280
That’s when you should start
culturing bhagavat-dharmā,

57
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:50,500
Kṛṣṇa consciousness.
 

